 MBOMBELA – Easter spells out rare beauty, the rare beauty of a new life. This quote by SD Gordon was proven true in the eyes of the kids who gathered at the centre court of Riverside Mall on Saturday. ALSO READ: Kiddies get into the spirit of Easter The children’s eyes lit up as they had the opportunity to paint their very own Easter eggs and their smiles grew even wider when they realised that they could eat them too. ALSO READ: Fabulous flavours titillate the taste buds Under the watchful eyes of childminders, the kids also had the opportunity to have their faces painted while their parents enjoyed a little Easter shopping. Narhan Unal said she and her sister, Ayesha, enjoyed the day very much and that they also made new friends. 